    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1962-02-19T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1962-02-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="278k"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d278k">
                <head>278K. Letter from <gloss target="#t_CIA_1">CIA</gloss> Director <persName
                        corresp="#p_MJA_1">McCone</persName> to <persName corresp="#p_DAW_1">Allen
                        W. Dulles</persName>, February 19<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d278kfn1"
                        >Survey of the Cuban operation. 1 p. Secret. <gloss target="#t_CIA_1"
                            >CIA</gloss>, <gloss target="#t_DCI_1">DCI</gloss> Files, History Staff
                        Files: Job 85–00664R. </note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-head" calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1962-02-19">February 19, 1962</date>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>Dear Allen:</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>I have received your memorandum of 15 February 1962 containing your comments on
                    the Inspector General’s Survey of the Cuban Operation. Copies of this
                    memorandum, together with the <gloss target="#t_DDP_1">DD/P</gloss> analysis of
                    the survey, the comments made by General <persName corresp="#p_CGCP_1"
                        >Cabell</persName>, Mr. Kirkpatrick, and the personal views expressed by Mr.
                        <persName corresp="#p_BCT_1">Tracy Barnes</persName>, will be bound in the
                    report—and therefore will be known to anyone who might have occasion to read
                    it.</p>
                <p>Sincerely,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed corresp="#p_MJA_1">
                        <persName corresp="#p_MJA_1">John A. McCone</persName>
                    </signed>
                    <affiliation>Director</affiliation>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
